• Beginning Accounts Receivable (from 2023-12-31): 0.00  
• Ending Accounts Receivable (from 2024-01-29): 1,604,015.21

Step 2: Calculate the Average Accounts Receivable.
Average Accounts Receivable = (Beginning AR + Ending AR) / 2  
= (0.00 + 1,604,015.21) / 2  
= 802,007.605

Step 3: Determine the Total Revenue.
From the income statement, Total Revenue (or Main Business Revenue) = 5,755,241.17

Step 4: Calculate the Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio.
Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio = Total Revenue / Average Accounts Receivable  
= 5,755,241.17 / 802,007.605  
≈ 7.17

Thus, the Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio is approximately 7.17.
